article.headline: Harvard 77, Dartmouth 71
article.story: BOSTON (AP) -- Brian Cusworth scored 20 points and grabbed a career-high 17 rebounds Friday to lead Harvard to a 77-71 win over Dartmouth. Alex Barrett led Dartmouth (6-8, 1-1 Ivy League) with 22 points and 11 rebounds. Leon Pattman added 13 points and Jason Meyer 12 for the Big Green. Jeremy Lin and Jim Goffredo each had 12 for Harvard (8-8, 1-1). Drew Hausman added 11 and Evan Harris and Brad Unger both scored 10. The Crimson fell behind 34-33 at halftime and saw the lead change hands 12 times before they pulled ahead 62-61 on Unger's jumper with 5:29 left. The win broke a four-game losing streak for the Crimson, who outrebounded Dartmouth 43-34. Harvard turned the ball over 17 times, good for 18 Dartmouth points. Dartmouth went on a 7-0 run four minutes into the second half to take a 45-39 lead on Barrett's jump shot at 14:03. Harvard answered with six unanswered points to tie it at 45-45 on Lin's consecutive baskets. The lead changed hands eight times before Harvard went on an 11-4 run, starting with Goffredo's second 3-pointer of the night, to pull ahead 68-63 with 3:06 left. Harvard held Dartmouth to eight points during the final 4:30.
